\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-f23f4f4\" data-id=\"f23f4f4\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bf428a9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bf428a9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ac6913c elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ac6913c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;zoomIn&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Our Testing Philosophy<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6c3dca6 elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6c3dca6\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;bounceInRight&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"p1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A testing philosophy is a set of beliefs and principles that guide the approach and methodologies used in software testing. It encompasses the overall strategy and mindset that a QA team adopts in order to ensure the quality and reliability of a software product. A testing philosophy can include a variety of elements such as the types of testing that should be performed, the level of testing required, and the testing tools and techniques that should be used.<\/span><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-dc70b65 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default wpr-particle-no wpr-jarallax-no wpr-parallax-no wpr-sticky-section-no\" data-id=\"dc70b65\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-f537d1d\" data-id=\"f537d1d\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-inner-section elementor-element elementor-element-bf27532 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default wpr-particle-no wpr-jarallax-no wpr-parallax-no wpr-sticky-section-no\" data-id=\"bf27532\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-inner-column elementor-element elementor-element-7403dc6\" data-id=\"7403dc6\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-66151ba elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"66151ba\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-141cea0 elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"141cea0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;zoomIn&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Common testing philosophies<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c3b8796 elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c3b8796\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;slideInLeft&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ol><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Agile testing philosophy:<\/strong> This philosophy emphasizes the importance of rapid feedback, early testing, and continuous integration in the software development process. It is based on the Agile software development methodology and focuses on testing as a collaborative effort between developers and QA teams.<\/span><\/li><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Exploratory testing philosophy:<\/strong> This philosophy emphasizes the importance of active testing, where the tester is free to explore the software product and find defects in an unstructured and informal manner. This approach can be useful for identifying unexpected defects that may not have been found through formal test cases.<\/span><\/li><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Test-driven development philosophy:<\/strong> This philosophy emphasizes the importance of writing test cases before any code is written. This helps ensure that the software meets the requirements and is of high quality.<\/span><\/li><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><strong>Shift-left testing philosophy:<\/strong> This philosophy emphasizes the importance of testing early in the software development process, in order to identify and fix defects as soon as possible. This can help reduce costs, improve quality, and speed up time to market.<\/span><\/li><\/ol>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8641d3d elementor-invisible elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"8641d3d\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_animation&quot;:&quot;bounceInRight&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>In summary, a testing philosophy is the set of beliefs and principles that guide the approach of QA teams in ensuring the quality and reliability of a software product. It can include elements like the types of testing that should be performed, the level of testing required and the testing tools and techniques that should be used.<\/p><p>When it comes to offshore QA teams, a testing philosophy that emphasizes clear communication, collaboration, and accountability can be particularly effective.<\/p><p>At Axium Solutions, testing is in our DNA and we handcraft testing solutions based on your needs whether is agile or exploratory or shift-left.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Our Testing Philosophy Our Testing Philosophy A testing philosophy is a set of beliefs and principles that guide the approach and methodologies used in software testing. It encompasses the overall strategy and mindset that a QA team adopts in order to ensure the quality and reliability of a software product. A testing philosophy can include [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"elementor_canvas","meta":[],"amp_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/axium.sol